Monte Carlo Simurations

Kei Sakamoto

Set the random seed, sample size, and true parametaers(sd(u)populationsesd)

set.seed(1234567)
n<-1000
b0<-1; b1<-0.5; su<-2

Draw a sample of size n

x <- rnorm(n,4,1) #xNormalx
u <- rnorm(n,0,su) #Normal0Normal
y <- b0 + b1*x + u #y

estimate parameters by OLS

(olsres <- lm(y~x))
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = y ~ x)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)            x  
##      1.2092       0.4384

features of the sample for the variance formula:

mean(x^2)
## [1] 16.96644
mean(x)
## [1] 3.997003
sum((x-mean(x))^2) #SSTx
## [1] 990.4104

217Var(1_hat)4/990consistent0

Graph

plot(x, y, col="gray", xlim=c(0,8) )
abline(b0,b1,lwd=2)
abline(olsres,col="gray",lwd=2)
legend("topleft",c("pop. regr. fct.","OLS regr. fct."),
                               lwd=2,col=c("black","gray"))
